The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ATP award for Chennai Open 

New Delhi: The Chennai Open has bagged the prestigious ATPs Player Services Award of excellence for its outstanding organisation and hospitality. 

The award was presented by ATP CEO Brad Drewett to Fernando Soler, tournament director of Chennai Open, at the recent international tournament directors meeting. 

Hailing the impressive organisational skills of the tournament, Drewett said: The Chennai Open has for many years had a strong reputation for its outstanding organisation and in particular wonderful hospitality towards the players. 

 (PTI) 




